Usage:

python receiver.py [Receive IP] [Receive port] [Window size]
python sender.py [Receive IP] [Receive port] [Window size]

for example:
python receiver.py 127.0.0.1 5050 4
python sender.py 127.0.0.1 5050 4

sender.py : Code for read the document and sending packets
receiver.py : Sending ACK, receive packets and write received data to file
Utility: classes for header, data packets, UnreliableSocket and some helping functions
RDTSocket: inherit UnreliableSocket, the implementation of the sockets
alice.txt: document to be sent
download.txt: document received from the sender


